  <p>
    Proper preparation before your regenerative medicine treatment is essential for optimal outcomes and safety. 
    Following these guidelines will help ensure your body is ready for the procedure and recovery process.
  </p>

  <h2>General Preparation Guidelines</h2>
  <p>These guidelines apply to all regenerative medicine treatments unless otherwise specified by your physician:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Stay well-hydrated by drinking plenty of water in the days leading up to your treatment</li>
    <li>Get adequate sleep (7-9 hours) for at least three nights before your procedure</li>
    <li>Eat nutritious meals and avoid excessive alcohol consumption</li>
    <li>Continue taking prescribed medications unless instructed otherwise</li>
    <li>Inform your physician of any changes in your health status</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Medication Guidelines</h2>
  <p>Certain medications may need to be adjusted before your treatment:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Anti-inflammatory medications (NSAIDs)</strong>: Discontinue ibuprofen, naproxen, and aspirin 7 days before treatment</li>
    <li><strong>Blood thinners</strong>: Continue as prescribed unless specifically instructed to stop by your physician</li>
    <li><strong>Supplements</strong>: Discontinue fish oil, vitamin E, and other blood-thinning supplements 5 days before treatment</li>
    <li><strong>Prescription medications</strong>: Continue all prescription medications unless otherwise directed</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Activity Restrictions</h2>
  <p>To optimize your body's readiness for treatment:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Avoid strenuous exercise 24 hours before your procedure</li>
    <li>Do not consume alcohol 48 hours before treatment</li>
    <li>Avoid smoking or nicotine products for at least 72 hours before treatment</li>
    <li>Limit caffeine intake on the day of treatment</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Day of Treatment</h2>
  <p>On the day of your procedure:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Eat a light, healthy breakfast if your treatment is scheduled after morning hours</li>
    <li>Wear comfortable, loose-fitting clothing that allows easy access to the treatment area</li>
    <li>Arrive 15 minutes early for check-in and preparation</li>
    <li>Bring a list of current medications and any relevant medical records</li>
    <li>Arrange for transportation if sedation will be used</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Special Considerations</h2>

  <h3>PRP Therapy Preparation</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Maintain good iron levels through iron-rich foods or supplements as recommended</li>
    <li>Avoid blood-thinning medications and supplements as outlined above</li>
    <li>Stay well-hydrated to ensure optimal blood draw</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Exosome Therapy Preparation</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Follow standard preparation guidelines</li>
    <li>Inform your physician of any recent infections or illness</li>
    <li>Ensure the injection site is clean and free from skin conditions</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>IV Therapy Preparation</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Stay well-hydrated before your appointment</li>
    <li>Eat a light meal 1-2 hours before treatment</li>
    <li>Wear clothing that allows easy access to your arms</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>What to Avoid</h2>
  <p>In the days leading up to your treatment, avoid:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Excessive sun exposure or sunburn in the treatment area</li>
    <li>New skincare products or treatments in the injection area</li>
    <li>Dental work or invasive procedures within 48 hours</li>
    <li>Excessive stress or lack of sleep</li>
    <li>Extreme temperatures (saunas, ice baths) 24 hours before treatment</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Questions and Concerns</h2>
  <p>
    If you have any questions about pre-treatment preparation or need clarification on any guidelines, 
